- For each word in the string parameter `sentence` that represents a price (a sequence of digits preceded by a dollar sign), apply a discount of the integer parameter `discount%` and update the word in the sentence.
- All updated prices should be represented with exactly two decimal places.
- The updated sentence should be returned as a string.
- The string parameter `sentence` has a length greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 100000.
- The string parameter `sentence` consists of lowercase English letters, digits, spaces, and the dollar sign '$'.
- The string parameter `sentence` does not have leading or trailing spaces.
- All words in the string parameter `sentence` are separated by a single space.
- All prices in the string parameter `sentence` will be positive numbers without leading zeros and will have at most 10 digits.
- The integer parameter `discount` is greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 100.